<HEADLINE> Khorkina Wins Women's All-around Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 2 (Xinhua) -- Svetlana Khorkina of Russia won the
women's individual all-around title after surviving a fall on
landing during the vault at the European gymnastics championships
in St Petersburg, Russia, on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Khorkina, winner of the all-around title at last year's world
championships, earned 38.624 points over the four different
apparatus, beating two Romanians, Simona Amanar and Claudia
Presecan to silver and bronze with 38.392 and 38.267, reports said
reaching here.
</P>
<P>
The 19-year-old Khorkina, who fell off the beam during the team
competition on Friday, came in with a near perfect routine on the
same apparatus on Saturday. She scored 9.787 to take the lead from
the start despite the fall after the vault.  
</P>
</TEXT>
