<HEADLINE> Shanghai to Hold International Wushu Expo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 2 (Xinhua) -- An international exposition for the
Chinese ancient sport of Wushu will be held in Shanghai from May
2-5.
</P>
<P>
A Wushu competition will also be staged in the same period,
with about 400 athletes from 50 countries and regions will compete
in 20 events.
</P>
<P>
Organizers hope the biennial exposition will promote exchange
in the sport and help strengthen the advance understanding between
different countries and regions. 
</P>
