<HEADLINE> China's Hanwei Wins ABC Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, May 2 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese club Hanwei beat
China Regal of Hong Kong, China, 71-70 in the final to win the
Asian Basketball Confederation (ABC) championship here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Han Wei's three-point specialist Liang Da helped to a 14-5 lead
four minutes into play but Regal soon staged a comeback.
</P>
<P>
With 10 seconds remaining on the clock and Hanwei leading
71-70, Regal's John Spenser received two free throws but failed to
score, handing the crown to Hanwei. 
</P>
</TEXT>
