<HEADLINE> Moderate Tremor Rocks Northeastern India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, May 2 (Xinhua) -- A moderate earthquake measuring
5.7 on the Richter Scale rocked some areas in northeastern India
Saturday, the Press Trust of India (PTI) reported.
</P>
<P>
The tremor, recorded by the Alipore Meteorological Department
in Calcutta at 02:06 p.m. (local time), lasted about one minute in
areas of Arunachal Pardesh and states of Manipur and Assam.
</P>
<P>
There were no immediate reports of casualties or damage.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the quake was 572 km north of Calcutta.
</P>
</TEXT>
