<HEADLINE> Iranian Leader Vows to Support Hamas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, May 2 (Xinhua) -- Iran's supreme leader Ayatollah Ali
Khamenei vowed Saturday to continue support to the Palestinian
Islamic Resistance Movement (Hamas) in its fighting against Israel.
</P>
<P>
"In our support for the Muslim nation of Palestine, we
won't be deterred by any political or propaganda pressures,"
he assured the visiting Hamas leader Sheikh Ahmad Yassin.
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA quoted Khamenei as saying that
 "so long as there is a struggle for god, it cannot be defeated by
any initiatives, ploys, politics or weapons, and as long as such a
spirit guides the Palestinian struggle, the victory over the enemy
(Israel) is a certainty.''
</P>
<P>
He also termed Israel as "the cancerous tumor created in the
Middle East by colonial powers."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Yassin said that Hamas would continue its struggle
for liberation of Palestine and not give up even an inch of the
Palestinian land, adding that "in the course of our struggles, we
will either achieve martyrdom or liberate the holy Qods
(Jerusalem)."
</P>
<P>
Praising Iran for its support for the Palestinian struggle
against Israeli occupation, Yassin said that Iran has adopted a
"principled and realistic stand" toward the Palestinian issue.
</P>
<P>
He also said that the Palestinian issue has concerned all the
Islamic states and freedom-loving nations, hoping that the Muslim
world would pool efforts in supporting the Palestinian nation.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Yassin also met with Iranian former President
Hashemi Rafsanjani.
</P>
<P>
Terming the stance adopted by Hamas with regard to the Israeli
aggressions as realistic, Rafsanjani urged unity and cooperation
among the Islamic states to help resolve the Palestinian issue.
</P>
<P>
Yassin arrived here Tuesday for a five-day visit on the fourth
leg of his five-nation tour, which has taken him to Egypt, Syria
and Qatar. He will go to Kuwait after winding up his visit to
Iran. 
</P>
</TEXT>
