<HEADLINE> Annan Winds up 4-Day Visit to Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, May 2 (Xinhua) -- United Nations Secretary
General Kofi Annan left here Saturday afternoon for Djibouti, the
second leg of his eight-nation east and central African tour,
after four-day stay in Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference, Annan said that his purpose of coming
to this part of Africa is to discuss with African leaders on how
to double efforts to resolve some of the conflicts affecting the
continent.
</P>
<P>
He called on African countries to work together to solve
peacefully the conflicts afflicting the continent, saying that
Africa should be able to fully exploit the resources in the
continent by avoiding conflicts among the nations.
</P>
<P>
He said African countries should work together to resolve
political crisis.
</P>
<P>
Annan hoped that he would solicit reactions from African
countries to his recent report on Africa to the UN Security
Council.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia is the first leg of Annan's first east and central
African tour.
</P>
<P>
During his stay here, he attended the International Conference
on African Women and Economic Development which was organized to
coincide with the 40th anniversary of the United Nations Economic
Commission for Africa (ECA).
</P>
<P>
He will conclude his 12-day eight-nation tour on May 10, 1998.
</P>
</TEXT>
