<HEADLINE> Survey: Greek Language Being Taught in 50 Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, May 2 (Xinhua) -- The Greek language, which is believed
to be one of the most difficult languages for foreigners to learn,
is now being taught at 900 departments of 500 universities in
about 50 countries around the world, according to a survey
conducted by the Greek Language Center Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The survey shows that most institutions offering Greek language
lessons are centered in the United States, while in Europe,
Germany tops the list.
</P>
<P>
For the past three years, the Thessaloniki-based center has
been recording organizations offering contemporary Greek studies
in the world in cooperation with the Greek ministries of culture
and education.  
</P>
</TEXT>
