<HEADLINE> Baghdad Hosts 5th Arab People's Forces Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, May 2 (Xinhua) -- The 5th Arab People's Forces
Conference opened Saturday in Baghdad with the participation of
500 Arab politicians, intellectuals and MPs.
</P>
<P>
President Saddam Hussein's representative, Vice President Taha
Yassin Ramadan hosted the three-day conference, which is under
the theme "with the help of a unified Arab struggle, we can lift
the sanctions imposed on Iraq and liberate Palestine."
</P>
<P>
In his speech to the opening ceremony, Ramadan expressed his
appreciation of the stance adopted by some Arab countries against
the U.S. threats and toward the lifting of U.N. embargo on Iraq
imposed after its invasion of Kuwait in 1990, stressing that such
stance embodied pan-Arab unity.
</P>
<P>
Ramadan confirmed Iraq's full compliance with all its
obligations set in relevant Security Council resolutions and
complete cooperation with hundreds of inspection teams in Iraq
over the past seven years.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, spies of the American Central Intelligence
Agency and army officers controlled the U.N. Special Commission
(UNSCOM), which is in charge of the weapons inspection in Iraq,
and endeavored to sabotage Iraq's national security and overthrow
its leadership.
</P>
<P>
The vice president pointed out whenever Iraq got ready to see
U.N. sanctions lifted, the U.S. agents in the UNSCOM would create
a crisis followed by the U.S. threat to use force to kill innocent
Iraqis and destroy symbols of civilization in Iraq.
</P>
<P>
He said Arabs should be aware of the double-standard policy
pursued by the U.S. in dealing with the Security Council
resolutions.
</P>
<P>
Ramadan said Iraqi leadership has decided to urge the Security
Council and all governments and parties concerned to implement
immediately Paragraph 22 of resolution 687 if they wanted to
maintain a balanced relationship between Iraq and the Security
Council.
</P>
<P>
The paragraph provides that sanctions imposed on Iraq should
be lifted once all its weapons of mass destruction have been
destroyed. But without an affirmative report by UNSCOM, the
sanctions will remain in place.
</P>
<P>
He made it clear that Iraq will make their enemies feel that
they have to pay a high price if they decide to keep the embargo
in place because Iraq has destroyed all weapons banned and the
world should now assume their responsibilities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
