<HEADLINE> Romania Draws up new privatization strategy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, May 2 (Xinhua) -- The Romanian new government has
drawn up a privatization strategy, putting emphasis on the quality
of privatization process.
</P>
<P>
According to Sorin Dimitriu, Minister of Privatization, 1998
will be the privatization year of big commercial companies. The
preparation of bank and big commercial company privatization will
include the increase in the nominal capital and the debt
restructuring. Big commercial companies like the iron and steel
works in Galati and Hunedoara will be restructured before being
privatized.
</P>
<P>
Dimitriu also said the new strategy stipulated that the whole
privatization responsibility be transferred from the government to
the State Ownership Fund. The Fund is to privatize about 1.500
Romanian enterprises in 1998, 12 percent of these being national
corporations.  
</P>
