<HEADLINE> Angang Reaches Milestone in Technological Upgrades </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, May 3 (Xinhua) -- Two converters refitted from open
hearth furnaces have recently entered operations in the second
steel mill operated by the Anshan Iron and Steel Company (Angang)
in northeast China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
The event represents a milestone for technological upgrades at
Angang, one of the nation's iron and steel giants.
</P>
<P>
The steelworks initiated a project to transform its open hearth
processing late last year.
</P>
<P>
An additional converter is expected to enter operations within
the year and will help Angang end its use of open hearth furnaces.
</P>
<P>
Angang's continuous cast ratio is expected to exceed 90 percent
during 1999.
</P>
<P>
When compared to open hearth furnaces, the converting process
is not only less costly, but also consumes less power and creates
less pollution. 
</P>
</TEXT>
