<HEADLINE> Hingis Wins Her First Clay Title in German </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, May 3 (Xinhua) -- Top-ranked Martina Hingis struggled to
hold off the tough Jana Novotna 6-3, 7-5 on Sunday, winning her
first title on European red clay in Hamburg of Germany.
</P>
<P>
Hingis needed four match points to finally beat the
second-seeded Novotna, ranked No 3 in the world, in a match
marked by sloppy play by both players. It was the third title of
the year for the 17-year-old Swiss.
</P>
<P>
The Czech is 12 years Hingis' senior.
</P>
<P>
Neither player was at her best. Novotna strayed from her usual
serve-and-volley game, staying behind a lot and using a slice
backhand in an attempt to unsettle Hingis.
</P>
<P>
Hingis served poorly, but Novotna could not capitalize and
Hingis finally won in 98 minutes. Novotna wasted three break
points in the last game. 
</P>
