<HEADLINE> Hu Jintao Equates Winning Youth To Winning the Future </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 3 (Xinhua) -- Senior Chinese Communist Party and
State leader Hu Jintao today equated winning young people to
winning the future.
</P>
<P>
Hu said that three generations of Chinese leadership with Mao
Zedong, Deng Xiaoping and Jiang Zemin at the core have placed
priority on issues related to youth as part of the strategic view
concerning the destiny of the state and Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
Hu, China's vice-president and member of the Standing Committee
of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party of China (CPC)
Central Committee, made the remarks during a meeting with
representatives of young award winners and volunteers in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Hu pointed to the forthcoming May 4th celebrations marking
the Youth Day, and expressed hope that young people will inherit and
display the glorious traditions of the May Fourth Movement to make
greater contributions to China's reform, development and stability.
</P>
<P>
Young students launched a nationwide anti-imperialism campaign
on May 4, 1919, as part of an effort to pressure the then Chinese
government into boycotting the foreign invasion.
</P>
<P>
Hu urged young Chinese to study hard, work diligently, be
willing to sacrifice and join in practical work. "Studying hard
is a major step enabling young people to make progress", said Hu.
</P>
<P>
He called on youngsters to study Deng Xiaoping Theory and learn
modern science and technology. 
</P>
</TEXT>
