<HEADLINE> Corner Stone Placed for Beijing University History Museum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 3 (Xinhua) -- The corner stone for a new
Beijing University History Museum was placed today at the site
near the university's picturesque Weiming Lake.
</P>
<P>
The museum is one of the key projects being undertaken to mark
the 100th anniversary of the founding of this prestigious
university which has its history closely linked with that of
modern China.
</P>
<P>
The two-story museum, covering over 3,000 sq.m., will include
research offices, exhibition halls, an archives, storage rooms and
computer rooms.
</P>
<P>
The facility is being constructed with a 270 million yen
donation from 69 Japanese enterprises. 
</P>
