<HEADLINE> Beijing University Unveils Statue Of Chinese Educator </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 3 (Xinhua) -- A bronze statue of Yan Fu
(1854-1921), one of the first presidents of Beijing University,
was unveiled today as part of activities to celebrate the
university's centenary anniversary.
</P>
<P>
The statue was funded by former Beijing University students
from east China's Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
Yan Fu is known as one of the most famous thinkers, translators
and educators in the nation's modern period.
</P>
<P>
Yan received his university diploma in Britain and became
president of Beijing University in 1912, the first year when the
university received its present name. The school was formerly
known as Jingshi Daxuetang, or Capital University.
</P>
<P>
The university campus is currently bustling with alumni from
different periods. At least 20,000 former students have returned
to the campus from all parts of the country and the world.
</P>
<P>
Volunteers wearing red vests guide visitors to campus-wide
celebration activities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
