<HEADLINE> Kaiserslautern Win League Title One Round Earlier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, May 3 (Xinhua) -- Kaiserslautern became the first
promoted club to win the German first division title in the
35-year-old Bundesliga history after they thrashed VfL Wolfsburg
4-0 on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Kaiserslautern, the winners of last season's second division
title, secured their championships after the victory by opening an
unassailable four-point advantage over the closest chasers Bayern
Munich.
</P>
<P>
Bayern, the defending title-holders, were held a goalless draw
away by MSV Duisburg, with one round left in this season in the
Bundesliga, and had to be contend with the second place.
</P>
<P>
Nicknamed "Red Devils", Kaiserslautern had won three previous
first division titles in 1951, 1953 and 1991.
</P>
<P>
Olaf Marschall scored a pair in the 24th and 55th minutes and
captain Martin Wagner in the 52nd minute and striker Juergen
Rische two minutes from the end contributed the others. 
</P>
</TEXT>
