<HEADLINE> Army ammunition Dump Destroyed in Northern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, May 3 (Xinhua) -- An explosion ripped through an army
ammunition dump in Northern Province of Sri Lanka Sunday,
destroying a large stock of weapons, informed sources here said.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the blast occurred near the headquarters of an
army brigade in Vavuniya District, about 260 km from Colombo.
</P>
<P>
A premature explosion of a hand grenade may have caused the
destruction, said the sources, adding that only one soldier was
injured, and there was no immediate estimate on the loss of
weapons.
</P>
<P>
The sources also said the weapons were to be issued to combat
troops further north of Vavuniya. 
</P>
