<HEADLINE> Uganda Army Nets 23 ADF Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, May 3 (Xinhua) -- The Uganda army has netted 23
members of the Allied Democratic Forces (ADF) in a series of
search and hunt operations carried out recently in the western
Kasese District.
</P>
<P>
" We have made a lot of success in our current operations
against the ADF rebels in the district," the New Vision newspaper
Sunday quoted Ugandan army Zonal Commander Nathan Mugisha as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The zonal commander based in Kasese town said: "We are doing
everything possible to eliminate the ADF rebels." Rebel suspects
will be prosecuted on charges of treason, he added.
</P>
<P>
The hunt operations followed two attacks by the rebels on an
army camp in Muhunga in which at least two soldiers were killed
and another injured.
</P>
<P>
The number of the ADF rebels, estimated to be round 1,500 in
november 1996, has been reduced to some 350 after a series of
heavy blows from the government forces.
</P>
<P>
The recent security pact signed between Uganda and the
Democratic Republic of Congo made it still harder for the rebels
to survive in the region. 
</P>
