<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Afghan Peace Talks Break Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, May 3 (Xinhua) -- The intra-Afghan peace talks
between the Taliban militia and the rival Northern Alliance broke
down Sunday as the Northern Alliance refused to talk with the
Taliban.
</P>
<P>
Acting Chief of the U.N. Peace Mission on Afghanistan James
Ngobi, who is also the co-chairman of the Afghan Steering
Committee meeting, told the reporters that there will no session
between the two Afghan warring factions Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Ngobi announced the suspension of the Afghan peace talks,
saying the two sides were unable to meet because of their sharp
divisions on certain issues.
