<HEADLINE> More Young Professionals Emerge in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 3 (Xinhua) -- Beijing now has 1,487 senior
professionals under 35 years of age, 25.6 times the figure
for 1992, the latest statistics show.
</P>
<P>
The city has trained many young high-level professionals in
recent years. Senior professionals older than 51 account
for 60 percent of Beijing's total, down from 81.2 percent in 1992,
said Xin Tieliang, deputy chief of the Beijing Personnel Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The statistics also indicate that Beijing has about 550,000
personnel in specialized fields. In addition, the numbers of
middle- and senior-level technicians and professionals have
increased greatly year by year, Xin said.
</P>
<P>
Professionals younger than 35 make up 43.7 percent of the total
in specialized fields in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Senior professionals are regarded as equal in status to
associate professors or professors in higher learning
institutions.  
</P>
</TEXT>
