<HEADLINE> Lanzhou Emerges As Northwest China Trade Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, May 3 (Xinhua) -- Lanzhou, capital of northwest
China's Gansu Province, has emerged as a regional trade center
thanks to extensive efforts carried out by the local government in
recent years.
</P>
<P>
Lanzhou had 326 markets and more than 67,000 shops by the end
of 1997, in addition to five commercial blocks and 10 large
wholesale markets. The city has the largest labor market in
northwest China.
</P>
<P>
The city is also a regional financial center, with a total of
1,094 banking institutions.
</P>
<P>
Local markets recorded a trade volume of 14.7 billion yuan in
1997. 
