<HEADLINE> Hunan Leads World in Mineral Resources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, May 3 (Xinhua) -- Recent statistics reveal that
central China's Hunan Province has verified reserves of 142
kinds of the world's 150 mineral ores.
</P>
<P>
The figures also indicate that the province ranks first in the
world in terms of verified reserves of tungsten, bismuth and
antimony. Hunan also leads the nation in reserves of seven
additional minerals.
</P>
<P>
The estimated value of the province's ore reserves exceeds
1,222.3 billion yuan (147.26 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The total 1997 output value of the local mineral industry
approached 100 billion yuan and accounted for some 29 percent of
the province's GNP.
</P>
<P>
Hunan has allocated over 10 million yuan for mineral resource
exploration over the past five years, with related efforts leading
to the discovery of 30-odd mineral deposits.  
</P>
