<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, May 3 (Xinhua) -- A strong earthquake measuring 5.4 on
the open-ended Richter scale jolted Izu Peninsula, southwest of
Tokyo, and nearby areas Sunday morning, the Meteorological Agency
said.
</P>
<P>
There were no immediate reports of casualties or damage. The
agency said there were no worries of tidal waves.
</P>
