<HEADLINE> Gore Arrives in Cairo for One-day Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, May 3 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Vice President Al Gore arrived
here early Sunday morning on a one-day visit to Egypt within the
context of his current Mideast tour.
</P>
<P>
He will hold talks with President Hosni Mubarak to add a fresh
impetus to bilateral ties and the Mideast peace-making, the Middle
East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Gore will get acquainted with Egypt's evaluation of the current
Mideast situation in advance of Monday's London meetings of
U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright with Palestinian leader
Yasser Arafat and Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu.
</P>
<P>
The London conference is meant to break the 14-month stalemate
in the Palestinian-Israeli negotiations which have been stalled
since March 1997 over Israeli settlement buildings in Arab East
Jerusalem and long-delayed redeployment from the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
Gore will also brief the Egyptian leader on his talks with
Netanyahu and Arafat during his tour of the region which has taken
him to Israel, Saudi Arabia and the Palestinian self-rule areas.
</P>
<P>
The U.S., the main peace-broker in the Mideast peace process,
has so far failed to persuade Israel to give in to a 13.1 percent
withdrawal plan after the Palestinians have endorsed it.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the peace-making, Egyptian and U.S. officials expect
the Mubarak-Gore meetings to invigorate bilateral economic
relations and the four sub-committees of the Egyptian-American
Presidential Council which "move at a slow pace and need a push."
</P>
<P>
The meetings between both sides will focus on means of
encouraging U.S. investments in Egypt and facilitating the entry
of Egyptian exports into the U.S.
</P>
<P>
Diplomatic sources said two agreements will be signed on the
sidelines of the meetings to promote cooperation in environment
and the medium and small industries. 
</P>
