</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980503.0141 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Post-Cultural Revolution Ideological Debate (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In August 1978 the debate reached a significant turning point
with the backing of local party leaders. The August 4 edition of
the "People's Daily" carried a news story on its front page,
titled "The Standing Committee of the CPC Heilongjiang Provincial
Committee Holds Enlarged Meeting to Discuss the Problem of Truth
Criterion".
</P>
<P>
The fact that a provincial Party committee openly supported and
took part in the debate on the criterion of truth in the news
media marked the beginning of a new stage in this debate.
Leaders in Xinjiang, Guangdong, Fujian and other regions
immediately followed suit and voiced their approval of the debate.
</P>
<P>
When the Central Work Conference was convened later in the
year, the debate had won the open backing of the principal leaders
in 21 provinces, municipalities and autonomous regions, more than
two-thirds of the country's total.
</P>
<P>
By that time, the preachers of the "two whatevers" found
themselves in a very isolated position, things labeled "Left" had
been losing popularity gradually, and the major debate on the
criterion of truth had become irreversible.
</P>
<P>
In the words of Shen Baoxiang, who has truthfully recorded the
whole debate, this new situation should be attributed to the
direct support of Deng Xiaoping and other revolutionary veterans,
careful organization by Hu Yaobang and other comrades,
participation of the broad masses of officials, especially senior
officials in various provinces, municipalities and autonomous
regions, as well as joint efforts of many theoreticians and journalists.
</P>
<P>
As the major debate on the criterion of truth developed
rapidly, the Central Work Conference was convened in Beijing on
November 10, 1978. Chen Yun, who spoke first at the conference in
line with the principle that practice is the sole criterion for
testing truth, raised some tough questions, including correcting
wrong decisions made by the late Mao Zedong, and won a warm
response from the participants.
</P>
<P>
On November 25 the CPC Central Committee decided that the CPC
Beijing Municipal Committee should announce the rehabilitation of
those involved in the "Tiananmen Incident", and that all
documents concerning "Counterattacking the Right Deviationist
Attempt to Reverse Correct Verdicts" aimed at Deng Xiaoping should
be annulled.
</P>
<P>
The Central Work Conference turned out to be a great success,
developing from a simple economic conference into a meeting that
helped bring order out of chaos.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980503.0142 </DOCNO>
