<HEADLINE> 30 Cambodian Refugees Killed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, May 3 (Xinhua) -- Some 30 Cambodian Khmer Rouge
dependents were killed and 20 others injured when they were trying
to flee the fighting in the country, news reaching here said
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Bangkok Post reported Sunday that an artillery shell which
might have been fired by Cambodian government forces, landed among
those trying to flee.
</P>
<P>
About 25,000 refugees, most of them Khmer rouge dependents,
have crossed into the northeastern areas of Thailand when
Cambodian government forces launched attacks at Khmer Rouge
positions.
</P>
<P>
