<DOCNO> XIE19980503.0149 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fiscal Reforms Top Agenda for New Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 3 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Finance has put the
transformation of China's numerous administrative charges and
other governmental fees into taxes at the top of the fiscal reform
agenda, says newly appointed finance minister Xiang Huaicheng.
</P>
<P>
Given that the number of fees charged by government
institutions places heavy burdens on Chinese people and
enterprises, the ministry has determined to standardize these
charges.
</P>
<P>
"We will abolish administrative charges and a large number of
unjustifiable fees," today's China Daily quoted Xiang as saying.
</P>
<P>
He said that some forms of necessary charges will be brought
within the realm of the taxation system rather than lying in the
wallets of government departments or local governments.
</P>
<P>
But items such as park admission fees and charges for services
provided on demand, such as the issuance of documents, are
expected to be retained.
</P>
<P>
Xiang said that the Ministry of Finance is collaborating with
the Economic Restructuring Office and the State Administration of
Taxation on the elaboration of the reform program.
</P>
<P>
"In the next five years, I will spare no efforts to improve the
management of the State coffers and upgrade the fiscal system,"
said Xiang, the former deputy director of the State Administration
of Taxation.
</P>
<P>
During his tenure, the finance ministry will aim to gradually
reduce the budget deficit, raise the ratio of fiscal revenue to
gross domestic product and increase the proportion of the central
government's income to the country's total.
</P>
<P>
Most importantly, fiscal work should concentrate on ensuring
the public fiscal target be met, guaranteeing social stability,
revitalizing China through science and education, and promoting
social and economic progress, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Finance will employ fiscal policies as macro
control measures to increase domestic demand and spur steady
economic growth.  
</P>
</TEXT>
