<HEADLINE> Panama Suspends Daily Power Cut </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, May 2 (Xinhua) -- Panamanian energy authorities
Friday announced the lift of a daily two-hour power suspension in
place for more than a year.
</P>
<P>
According to the Hydraulic Resources and Electrification
Institute (IRHE), water levels in the reservoirs of Fortuna and
Bayano have improved considerably following serious drought in
Panama caused by the El Nino effect.
</P>
<P>
Power produced by hydroelectric stations accounts for 65
percent of the electricity output in Panama.
</P>
<P>
The IRHE urged businessmen and the public sector to continue
energy saving programs to maintain the daily consuming quota of
11,500 MWH.
</P>
<P>
The Panamanian government spent three million U.S. dollars in
the past year on purchasing power from neighboring countries.
</P>
