<HEADLINE> Mexico, El Salvador To Strengthen Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, May 2 (Xinhua) -- Mexico and El Salvador have
agreed to strengthen cooperation in cultural, technical and
scientific areas in the next three years, the Mexican Foreign
Affairs Ministry said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
An agreement was reached in the first meeting of the Joint
Educational and Cultural Cooperation Commission and also the first
meeting of the Joint Technical and Scientific Cooperation
Commission of the two countries.
</P>
