<HEADLINE> Germany Takes Two Golds At European Weightlifting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, May 2 (Xinhua) -- Germany won two gold medal at stake in
the European weightlifting championships in Riesa, Germany on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The host country only took one gold medal after the first four
days of the event, through Monique Riesterer in the women's 75
kilograms class on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Marc Huster of Germany won the men's 85-kg class with a total
lift of 382.5 kgs, beating Olympic champion Pyrros Dimas of Greece
and Turkey's Dursun Sevinc into second and third places
respectively.
</P>
<P>
In the 94-kg category, German Oliver Caruso delighted more than
1,000 spectators by winning another gold.
</P>
<P>
Olympic bronze medallist Caruso dominated the field in both
the snatch and the clean and jerk for a total winning lift of
395.0 kgs.
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria's Ivan Tschakarov took the silver and Akakios
Kakiashvilis of Greece the bronze.
</P>
<P>
The championships will end on Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
