<HEADLINE> Moderate Quake Jolts Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, May 3 (Xinhua) -- A moderate earthquake which lasted for
about 50 seconds jolted Bangladesh on Saturday afternoon, media
reports said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The intensity of the tremor, which started at about 2:38:37
p.m. (local time) and hit the capital city of Dhaka and the
country's southeastern port city of Chittagong, was "moderate,"
the reports quoted meteorologists here as saying.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the quake was some 480 kilometers off
Chittagong, according to the observatory at Chittagong. The tremor
was also felt in other parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
There was no report of damage or casualties from the tremor-hit
areas till now. 
</P>
</TEXT>
