<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT, May 3 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH -- Cambodian King Norodom Sihanouk met here Saturday
with Second Prime Minister and Vice-President of the Cambodian
People's Party Hun Sen to discuss political issues.
</P>
<P>
After the talks, Hun Sen advised media representatives that he
had reported on the situation and conditions in the country to the
king. He said they also discussed the forthcoming elections and
the progress that had been made so far.
</P>
<P>
"I have reported to his majesty the King that I and the royal
Cambodian government will try our best to make the upcoming
elections free, fair and credible, and without violence," Hun Sen
said. (Cambodia-Sihanouk-Hun Sen)
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA -- United Nations Secretary General Kofi Annan left
here Saturday afternoon for Djibouti, the second leg of his
eight-nation east and central African tour, after four-day stay in
Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference, Annan said that his purpose of coming to
this part of Africa is to discuss with African leaders on how to
double efforts to resolve some of the conflicts affecting the
continent.
</P>
<P>
He called on African countries to work together to solve
peacefully the conflicts afflicting the continent, saying that
Africa should be able to fully exploit the resources in the
continent by avoiding conflicts among the nations. (Ethiopia-Annan
Visit)
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- The delegation of the Afghan Taliban militia to
the current round of intra-Afghan peace talks will not come back
to Islamabad for Sunday's meeting, a senior Taliban official here
told Xinhua Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban representative to Islamabad, Abdul Hakeem Mujahid,
said he himself would represent the Taliban at the talks and would
 be accompanied by some other Taliban officials based in the
Pakistani capital. (Afghan-Talks-Taliban)
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
