<HEADLINE> Finns Defeats Latvia 6-0 at Ice Hockey Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, May 2 (Xinhua) -- Finland crushed Latvia 6-0 in their
Group D opening match held in Basle at the world ice hockey
championship on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Olympic bronze medallists went into the tournament without
top players Teemu Selanne and Saku Koivu but still proved too
strong for the Latvians, playing in the world group for only the
second time.
</P>
<P>
Jere Karalahti opened the scoring late in the first period and
the second period saw the Finnish offence going rampant with five
different scorers beating Latvian goalie Arturs Irbe in less than
10 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Russia beat Kazakhstan 8-4 in another Group D match.
</P>
<P>
In two Group C games, The united States outplayed Switzerland
5-2 and Sweden ousted France 6-1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
