<HEADLINE> France's Cherifi Takes WBC Middleweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 2 (Xinhua) -- French boxer Hacine Cherifi defeated
Keith Holmes of the United States on a unanimous points decision
in his hometown Lyon to win the World Boxing Council (WBC)
middleweight title on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Thirty-year-old Cherifi is the first Frenchman in 50 years to
win a world title in the prestigious middleweight category.
</P>
<P>
Cherifi employed from-the-close-range tatics to hand Holmes
only his second defeat in 33 bouts.
</P>
<P>
Shortly afterwards, in the same ring, another Frenchman,
Fabrice Tiozzo, easily retained his WBA cruiserweight crown by
stopping American Terry Ray in less than a minute. 
</P>
</TEXT>
