<HEADLINE> De Bruin Beats Irish 800 Meters Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 2 (Xinhua) -- Triple Olympic champion Michelle de
Bruin beat the Irish 800 meters freestyle record at a swimming
meeting near Paris on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Irish swimmer, currently embroiled in doping allegations,
won the 800 final in eight minutes 40.01 seconds.
</P>
<P>
The International Amateur Swimming Federation (FINA) said on
Wednesday a urine sample given by De Bruin in January showed
"unequivocal signs of adulteration". De Bruin later denied she
had tampered with the sample.
</P>
<P>
De Bruin won three gold medals at the 1996 Atlanta Olympics
under her maiden name of Smith. 
