<HEADLINE> Panamanian Comptroller, Commerce Minister Resign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, May 2 (Xinhua) -- Panamanian General Comptroller
Aristides Romero and Commerce and Industry Minister Raul Arango
resigned Friday, sources from the Presidency said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Romero, uncle of Panamanian President Ernesto Perez Balladares,
said in a brief statement that his resignation was due to "health
reasons." He will be temporarily replaced by Vice-Comptroller
Gustavo Perez.
</P>
<P>
The sources said Arango resigned to occupy himself in party
politics as a member of the National Liberal Party, a coalition in
which he is the top figure.
</P>
<P>
Raul Hernandez, vice president of the National Liberal Party,
might be a candidate to replace Arango as the commerce and
industry minister, the sources said. 
