<HEADLINE> Paris St. Germain Beats Lenz to Win French Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 2 (Xinhua) -- Paris Saint Germain edged the French
league leaders Lenz 2-1 for its fifth French Cup title in the
Stade de France Stadium on Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
Brazilian midfield Rai opened the accounting for PSG in the
25th minute and Italian forward Marco Simone doubled the leading
margin eight minutes after the second half.
</P>
<P>
Lenz, on the brink of its first league title when the matches
end next week, pulled back one goal with seven minutes remaining
through Czech Vladimir Smicer, but that was too late to be good.
</P>
<P>
The win gave PSG a rare cup double after they took home the
French League Cup on April 4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
